-- TA Triumph-Adler Says Chief Executive Officer Leaving for Health Reasons
-- Mike Gavin
-- 2010-07-20T14:56:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-20/ta-triumph-adler-says-chief-executive-officer-leaving-for-health-reasons.html

          
          
             TA Triumph-Adler said Chief
Executive Officer Robert Feldmeier will step down due to health
reasons, effective as of Sept. 1, 2010. Takashi Kuki, the
president of Kyocera Mita B.V., will be seconded to the
management board to act as CEO, TA Triumph-Adler said.  
          
          


  


        